You should create instance of [Socket][1]  
[get output stream][2] and write to it (e.g. with [ObjectOutputStream][3]).  

    Socket echoSocket = new Socket(hostName, portNumber);
    ObjectOutputStream out = new ObjectOutputStream(echoSocket.getOutputStream());
    out.writeObject(names);  
You can find an example in Oracle docs: [example][4] 


  [1]: http://docs.oracle.com/javase/7/docs/api/java/net/Socket.html
  [2]: http://docs.oracle.com/javase/7/docs/api/java/net/Socket.html#getOutputStream%28%29
  [3]: http://docs.oracle.com/javase/7/docs/api/java/io/ObjectOutputStream.html
  [4]: http://docs.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/networking/sockets/readingWriting.html
